This paper discusses the quantitative analysis of scientific communication, which is relevant to several sub-fields in computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which focuses on the organization, retrieval, and analysis of digital information. The paper also discusses citation analysis, which is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses visualization and mapping of science, which is relevant to cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
